main event: The UFO report describes a radar observation of an unidentified flying object with maneuvers conducted over a 4-minute period.
interesting points: The observation took place at 2207 local time.
The observed course of the UFO was from 45 degrees 38'N - 110 degrees 38'E to 45.6 degrees - 34'N - 110 degrees -40'E.
The report suggests that the observed maneuvers were likely performed by a Soviet aircraft, although the details are redacted.
The report is dated 9 January AFM Point 3949 (4 Jan 52).
The observation was conducted using radar.
